{
  "doc_id": "51715",
  "text": "First, although face-space is likely coded in posterior face areas [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , the problem in some individuals with DP appears to be not in these areas but instead in weak connections from these areas to anterior face areas [CITATION_3] . This means that failure to find abnormal aftereffects in individuals with DP does not rule out an association between face-space coding and face recognition within the normal population, in whom the forward connections are intact. Thus, in the present study, we tested only individuals in the normal range of face recognition ability.",
